## Using the REST Client extension to test our code

## AUTH TESTS 

### Register a new user
POST http://localhost:5117/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "username": "testuser",
  "email": "testuser@example.com",
  "password": "123456"
}

### Login with an existing user
POST http://localhost:5117/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "testuser@example.com",
  "password": "123456"
}

# After login, copy the token from the response and replace <YOUR_JWT_HERE>
# Example: Authorization: Bearer <YOUR_JWT_HERE>

## NOTE TESTS CRUD

### Create a new note
POST http://localhost:5117/api/notes
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer <YOUR_JWT_HERE>

{
  "title": "My second note",
  "content": "This is a test note"
}

### Get all notes for the user
GET http://localhost:5117/api/notes
Authorization: Bearer <YOUR_JWT_HERE>

### Get a single note by ID
# Replace <NOTE_ID> with the _id from the "Get all notes" response
GET http://localhost:5117/api/notes/<NOTE_ID>
Authorization: Bearer <YOUR_JWT_HERE>

### Update a note
# Replace <NOTE_ID> with the _id from the "Get all notes" response
PUT http://localhost:5117/api/notes/<NOTE_ID>
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer <YOUR_JWT_HERE>

{
  "title": "Updated note title",
  "content": "Updated content"
}

### Delete a note
# Replace <NOTE_ID> with the _id from the "Get all notes" response
DELETE http://localhost:5117/api/notes/<NOTE_ID>
Authorization: Bearer <YOUR_JWT_HERE>
